'''David Storobin''' is a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] represents District 27 in the [[New York State Senate]], which comprises Bergen Beach, [[Flatlands]], [[Mill Basin]], [[Sheepshead Bay]], and [[Midwood]], among other neighborhoods found within the [[New York City]] borough of [[Brooklyn]].

==Biography==
Born in [[Caucasus]] near [[Russia]], he came to America with his mother and has strongly opposed same-gender marrages and promoted Jewish values.  He won over city councilman [[Lewis Fidler]] in a very close election.<ref>[http://brooklyn.ny1.com/content/top_stories/162251/storobin-declared-winner-in-special-state-senate-election Storobin Declared Winner In Special State Senate Election]</ref><ref>[http://online.wsj.com/article/APec43cb598d20435db5f50991c6f15f97.html Storobin emerges as winner in NY special election] ''[[The Wall Street Journal|Wall Street Journal]]''</ref>  The election was held to replace [[Carl Kruger]] who was accused of bribery and forced to resign. 

